// paper Cube

#include <iostream>
#include <cstdio>
#include <cstring>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

int main()
{
	 int t;
	 scanf("%d",&t);
	 while(t--)
	 {
				  int arr[6][6];
				  int r[6] = {0}, c[6] = {0};
				  bool f = false;
				  for(int i = 0; i < 6; ++i)
					 for(int j = 0; j < 6; ++j)
					 			{
									 int temp;
									 scanf("%d",&temp);
									 arr[i][j] = temp;
									 if(arr[i][j]){r[i]++; c[j]++;}
	  				 			}
					 for(int i = 0; i < 6; ++i)
					  for(int j = 0; j < 6; ++j)
						{
								 if(arr[i][j] && ((r[i] == 3 && c[j] == 4) || (r[i] == 4 && c[j] == 3)))
								              {f = true; break;}
		 		 		}
					  if(f)printf("correct\n");
					  else printf("incorrect\n");
  	 }
  	 return 0;
}
